3.2. Asia–Pacific
The Asia–Pacific region extends from Mongolia in the north to New Zealand in the south and reaches beyond India to Pakistan in the west (see Figure 3). Of the approximately 134 million births in 2023 (latest reliable statistics), over 43% (57.5 million) are born in the Asia–Pacific region. Three of the four countries with the most births are included in the region—1. India, 2. China, and 4. Pakistan. Across the region there are large variations in country sizes, economics, governmental structure, languages, and cultural sensitivities, each presenting a different challenge with respect to establishing and maintaining sustainable NBS. Vast size differences exist and geographic obstacles including mountains, deserts, and islands create unique opportunities for creativity in NBS service delivery.
