3.3. Europe
For our report and consistent with the 2021 update on NBS in Europe [668], we will consider Europe to consist of 54 countries, which includes Russia and five former Russia republics east of the Ural Mountains (Kazakhstan, Kyrgyzstan, Tajikistan, Turkmenistan, Uzbekistan), even though Europe is generally considered to end at the Urals. The total population of these countries is around 924 million, with about 10 million births annually. Note that the smaller countries of Andorra, Liechtenstein, Monaco, and San Marino have
Abbreviations: SAR = Special Administrative Region; PDR—Peoples’ Democratic Republic • More than 50% coverage; part of national or administrative region implementation/law
